  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "`this.refs` should always be an object. A component without currently-rendered refs should just have an empty `refs` object.\n\nCurrently, you have to guard for dynamic refs:\n\n``` js\nif (this.refs && this.refs.foo)\n```\n\nFor example, in a searchable component where the search input only appears once the contents reach a certain length:\n\n``` js\ncomponentDidUpdate: function(prevProps, prevState) {\n  var len = this.state.options.length;\n  var min = this.props.searchLength;\n  var search = this.refs && this.refs.search;\n  if (len > min && search) {\n    search.getDOMNode().focus();\n  }\n}\n```\n",
